
## linux cli (command line interface) shortcuts ##

# 1 - \Ctrl + a     --> HOME
# 2 - \Ctrl + e     --> END
# 3 - \Ctrl + h     --> [backspace] <--
# 4 - \Ctrl + l     --> clear
# 5 - \Ctrl + r     --> search history 
# 6 - \Ctrl + k     --> delete til END
# 7 - \Ctrl + w     --> delete word
# 8 - \Ctrl + u     --> delete til HOME
# 9 - \Ctrl + f     --> move (forward) one char
# 10 - \Ctrl + d     --> delete char to the right

# 10 - \Ctrl + d     --> delete char to the right
# 11 - \Ctrl + t     --> replace char left of cursor with right char
# 12 - \Ctrl + y     --> paste clipboard
# 13 - \Ctrl + b     --> move (backwards) one char
# 14 - \Ctrl + p     --> ?
